name: fish oil to generic market for energy feed | energy feed, gross | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/19153/documentation

This activity is a linking activity, i.e. it connects fish oil  with the generic market for energy feed. Fish oil is used partially as a feed for animals, thus traded on generic feed market with other protein - containing products.

The activity starts with the reception of fish oil.

Valid for all linking activities: The activity models the part of fish oil which contributes to the generic market for energy feed.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds

exchanges.description:
Calculated based on literature value for fish oil, 38.6 MJ/kg DM. Cross reference is 39 MJ/kg DM as reported in the Feedipedia.
